{
  "info": {
    "name": "diary — Autorización sin roles (PUCE)",
    "description": "Clase 'Mi Diario Privado'. Pega el access_token de ana en la variable {{token_ana}} y el de beto en {{token_beto}} (Hosted UI de Cognito → access_token, NO el id_token).",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url", "value": "http://localhost:8787" },
    { "key": "token_ana", "value": "PEGA_AQUI_EL_ACCESS_TOKEN_DE_ANA" },
    { "key": "token_beto", "value": "PEGA_AQUI_EL_ACCESS_TOKEN_DE_BETO" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "0. Sin token → 401",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /entries (sin token) → 401",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/entries", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["entries"] },
            "description": "No hay endpoints públicos. Ni uno."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /entries?author=ana (el viejo agujero) → 401",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/entries?author=ana",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["entries"],
              "query": [{ "key": "author", "value": "ana" }]
            },
            "description": "El ?author= ya no existe: el 'yo' lo define el token."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "1. Ana",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /me (ana) → email NULL 👀",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token_ana}}" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/me", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["me"] },
            "description": "El email sale null: viaja en el id_token, no en el access_token."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /entries (ana escribe)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token_ana}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"title\": \"Martes horrible\",\n  \"body\": \"Me fue pésimo en el examen y después...\",\n  \"author\": \"beto\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/entries", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["entries"] },
            "description": "Fíjate que el body intenta colar author: beto. Jackson lo IGNORA — lo que no está en el DTO, no existe. La entrada queda firmada por ana."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /entries (ana ve solo las suyas)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token_ana}}" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/entries", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["entries"] },
            "description": "Sin un solo parámetro. Y aun así sabe qué devolver."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /entries/1 (ana lee la suya) → 200",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token_ana}}" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/entries/1", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["entries", "1"] }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "2. Beto — el momento de la clase 🔥",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /entries (beto ve solo las suyas)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token_beto}}" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/entries", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["entries"] },
            "description": "MISMA URL que la de ana. Sin parámetros. Y devuelve cosas distintas."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /entries/1 (beto pide la de ANA) → 403 🔥",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token_beto}}" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/entries/1", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["entries", "1"] },
            "description": "Beto tiene un token válido y NO hay roles en esta app: Spring Security aprobó la petición. ¿Quién le dijo que no? TU `if` en el service."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "DELETE /entries/1 (beto borra la de ANA) → 403",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token_beto}}" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/entries/1", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["entries", "1"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /entries/999 (no existe) → 404",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token_ana}}" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/entries/999", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["entries", "999"] },
            "description": "404 = no existe para nadie. 403 = existe, pero no es tuya. No las confundas."
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
